:'''Phainon:''' Hey, mom. I'm home.
:'''Audata:''' Hehe, look at your expression... got your bags all packed?
:'''Phainon:''' Can't hide anything from you, huh... Yeah, I'm all set. Heading out the day after tomorrow.
:'''Audata:''' You've always been easy to read, my sweet child. Since you were little, I just had to glance your way to know what's on your mind.
:'''Audata:''' You said... you're going to Castrum Kremnos, right? I wonder how far that is from our Aedes Elysiae?
:'''Phainon:''' Haha, no clue. I heard that Castrum Kremnos roams around slowly, just like a dromas.
:'''Phainon:''' Don't worry, mom. Once I finish my studies, I'll come straight home. Who knows? Maybe one day that city will wander right past our village.
:'''Audata:''' Then I'll have to keep watch from the haystack. Just to see if a mountain-sized dromas is headed for Aedes Elysiae.
:'''Audata:''' When that day comes, your dad and I will fire up the stove, get a feast ready. You'll see the golden fields, the kitchen smoke curling &mdash; and know you're home.
:'''Phainon:''' Hah, even without the smoke, I'll always know where home is. I know these wheat fields better than anyone &mdash; except dad, maybe.
:'''Phainon:''' When I get back... I want honey suncake, with smoked venison and olive juice!
:'''Audata:''' Knew you'd say that. And if you make any friends, bring them home. The whole village will throw a proper feast to welcome them.
:'''Phainon:''' You got it! I can't help wondering the people I'll meet out there.
:'''Audata:''' Hehe... I believe in you. You'll definitely find kind, sincere people to walk beside you.
:'''Audata:''' Just remember to treat them with the same kindness. Never let their hearts go cold or hopes turn sour, okay?
:'''Phainon:''' Ah...
:'''Phainon:''' I won't, mom. I won't let anyone down... not them, not you, and not Dad.
